1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the outer bound of a broadcast channel, which is a topic in information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses a communication channel between two receivers, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture.
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the transmission of information between two receivers, which can be related to social and information networks.
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve computational complexity in deriving the outer bound for the broadcast channel.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may involve the transmission of multimedia content over the broadcast channel.
